				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>The large-scale investment by Chinese company Complant appears to be part of a wider strategy to move the Jamaican sugar sector up the value chain and reorient sugar production towards serving regional markets. This raises the question about the longer-term future of the current sugar-trade relationship with the EU. The Jamaica-Complant strategy will hinge critically upon the outcome of the feasibility study for the Frome refinery: if this proves unfavourable, then shifting the sector up the value chain to serve regional markets for direct-consumption sugars will prove non-viable.</p>
		</div>
		
